  "prompt": "Which countries recognize the Moroccan Degree in Medecine?",
  "response": "The recognition of medical degrees can vary significantly from one country to another and is often subject to specific regulations and agreements. As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, countries that typically recognize Moroccan medical degrees include some countries in Africa and the Middle East. However, many countries require foreign medical graduates to go through an equivalency process or take qualifying examinations before they are allowed to practice medicine.\n\nTo determine the specific countries that recognize Moroccan medical degrees, it is crucial to consult the relevant medical boards or educational authorities in the country of interest. Additionally, contacting the Moroccan Ministry of Higher Education or the individual medical schools in Morocco can provide updated and specific information regarding international recognition of their degrees.\n\nIf you have a particular country in mind, I can try to give more tailored guidance based on that.",
